<paragraph id="8BB7368AD86CFFE33CB4FDE330D1F9EA" blockId="57.[151,1058,601,652]" pageId="57" pageNumber="1016">
D i a g n o s i s: This is the only known species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C084D09D86CFFE33EFAFDE3316AF908" authorityName="Pic" authorityYear="1950" box="[729,853,601,622]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Pujoliclerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="57" pageNumber="1019" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97CEA98D86CFFE33EFAFDE3316AF908" box="[729,853,601,622]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="1016">Pujoliclerus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="F31F761AD86CFFE33FBFFDE331D2F909" box="[924,1005,601,623]" name="Mexico" pageId="57" pageNumber="1016">Mexico</collectingCountry>
. The genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C084D09D86CFFE33CFBFDCC336BF9ED" authorityName="Pic" authorityYear="1950" box="[216,340,630,651]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Pujoliclerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="57" pageNumber="1019" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97CEA98D86CFFE33CFBFDCC336BF9ED" box="[216,340,630,651]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="1016">Pujoliclerus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
PIC was revised in 2014 (
<bibRefCitation id="EF994B7BD86CFFE33E78FDCC30DCF9EA" author="OPITZ W" box="[603,739,630,652]" pageId="57" pageNumber="1016" pagination="727 - 756" refId="ref53564" refString="OPITZ W. (2014 d): Classification, natural history, and evolution of the checkered beetle genus Pujoliclerus PIC (Coleoptera: Cleridae: Peloniinae). - The Coleopteristss Bulletin 68 (4): 727 - 756." type="journal article" year="2014">OPITZ 2014d</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB7368AD86CFFE33CB4FD2132CCF882" blockId="57.[151,1059,666,996]" pageId="57" pageNumber="1016">
D e s c r i p t i o n: Size: Length 
<quantity id="4CF09B6FD86CFFE33E27FD20306AF9D6" box="[516,597,666,688]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.2" pageId="57" pageNumber="1016" unit="mm" value="4.2">4.2 mm</quantity>
; width 
<quantity id="4CF09B6FD86CFFE33E82FD2030CEF9D6" box="[673,753,666,688]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="57" pageNumber="1016" unit="mm" value="1.5">1.5 mm</quantity>
. Form: As in 
<figureCitation id="13332A0FD86CFFE33F5CFD2031EBF9D6" box="[895,980,666,688]" captionStart="Figs 346-349" captionStartId="114.[151,191,1496,1518]" captionTargetBox="[151,1058,195,1478]" captionTargetId="figure@114.[151,1059,195,1478]" captionTargetPageId="114" captionText="Figs 346-349: Habitus; (346) Pujoliclerus mexicoensis; (347) P. sentus; (348) P. testudinatus; (349) P. trunculus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3746836" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3746836/files/figure.png" pageId="57" pageNumber="1016">Fig. 346</figureCitation>
. Color: Cranium and antenna brown; prothorax mostly brown, pronotal disc shows broad black incised macula; pterothorax and abdomen dark brown; elytra mostly dark brown, epipleural and sutural margins testaceous; prothoracic legs brown, mesothoracic and metathoracic legs testaceous. Head: Cranium coarsely punctate; antenna (
<figureCitation id="13332A0FD86CFFE33FEBFCB03624F846" box="[968,1051,778,800]" captionStart="Figs 1-27" captionStartId="70.[151,191,1302,1324]" captionTargetBox="[155,1057,207,1268]" captionTargetId="figure@70.[155,1058,207,1283]" captionTargetPageId="70" captionText="Figs 1-27: Antennae; (1) Aphelocerus nodus; (2) A. copanus; (3) A. magnipannus; (4) A. yoro; (5) A. sparicapillus; (6) A. tigra. (7) A. nolus; (8) A. ligulus; (9) Perilypus schusteri; (10) P. apunctus; (11) P. virgulatus; (12) P. izabal; (13) P. alpinus; (14) Cregya fuscomacula; (15) Phonius versus; (16) Pujoliclerus ariquemes; (17) Pelonium falcatum; (18) Pujoliclerus cnecostus; (19) P. trunculus. (20) P. sentus; (21) P. testudinatus; (22) P. catie; (23) P. flavidus; (24) P. convexus; (25) P. meloinus; (26) P. mexicoensis; (27) P. tuxtlas." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3746746" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3746746/files/figure.png" pageId="57" pageNumber="1016">Fig. 26</figureCitation>
) capitate, funicular antennomeres decreasing in length to capitulum, 6 
<superScript id="7C7D9BC2D86CFFE33FA5FC9831ACF856" attach="left" box="[902,915,802,816]" fontSize="6" pageId="57" pageNumber="1016">th</superScript>
antennomere expanded, capitular antennomeres 8 and 9 triangular, antennomere 10 ovate; eyes large, coarsely facetted, eye wider than frons (EW/FW 30/20). Thorax: Pronotum (
<figureCitation id="13332A0FD86CFFE33FE2FCE43624F812" box="[961,1051,862,884]" captionStart="Figs 134-152" captionStartId="77.[151,191,1476,1498]" captionTargetBox="[183,1049,204,1454]" captionTargetId="figure@77.[152,1060,199,1462]" captionTargetPageId="77" captionText="Figs 134-152: Pronota; (134) Pujoliclerus catie; (135) P. mexicoensis; (136) P. convexus; (137) P. testudinatus; (138) Madoniella selvanegra; (139) Cregya entrerios; (140) Pujoliclerus trunculus; (141) P. sentus; (142) P. meloinus; (143) Sicamus suprus; (144) Nepsudia guenda; (145) Nanoclerus fuscus; (146) Topainca pachacutii; (147) Eurycaulis anaxeis; (148) Kataspinula puebla; (149) Madoniella muralla; (150) M. nota; (151) M. acicula; (152) M. baja." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3746760" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3746760/files/figure.png" pageId="57" pageNumber="1016">Fig. 135</figureCitation>
) slightly oblong (PW/PL 65/70), disc coarsely punctate, lateral tubercles well developed; elytral asetiferous punctures organized into 10 striae, punctures diminish in elytral posterior 3/4 
<superScript id="7C7D9BC2D86CFFE33D3BFC14331AF8DA" attach="left" box="[280,293,942,956]" fontSize="6" pageId="57" pageNumber="1016">th</superScript>
(EL/EW 170/40). Abdomen: Pygidium quadrate 
<emphasis id="B97CEA98D86CFFE33F3BFC083120F8AE" bold="true" box="[792,799,946,968]" pageId="57" pageNumber="1016">/</emphasis>
scutiform; aedeagus as in 
<figureCitation id="13332A0FD86CFFE33CB4FC7432CCF882" box="[151,243,974,996]" captionStart="Figs 249-254" captionStartId="91.[151,191,1289,1311]" captionTargetBox="[155,1061,201,1276]" captionTargetId="figure@91.[155,1061,201,1276]" captionTargetPageId="91" captionText="Figs 249-254: Aedeagi; (249) Pujoliclerus catie; (250) P. dexus; (251) P. meloinus; (252) P. mexicoensis (253) P. testudinatus (254) P. trunculus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3746788" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3746788/files/figure.png" pageId="57" pageNumber="1016">Fig. 252.</figureCitation>
</paragraph>
